<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chap_IMT">
  <title>The Invertible Matrix Theorem</title>
  <introduction>
    <objectives>
      <introduction>
        <p>
          By the end of this section, you should be able to give precise and thorough
          answers to the questions listed below. You may want to keep these questions
          in mind to focus your thoughts as you complete the section.
        </p>
      </introduction>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            What does it mean for two statements to be equivalent?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How can we efficiently prove that a string of statements are all equivalent?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the Invertible Matrix Theorem and why is it important?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What are the equivalent conditions to a matrix being invertible?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
